    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of casualty figures cited in May 30 article about sculpture at National D-Day Memorial in Bedford, Va; also, sculptor is James Brothers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article by The Associated Press on Tuesday about the unveiling of a sculpture at the National D-Day Memorial in Bedford, Va., misstated Allied losses on D-Day. American casualties of 6,603 included not only those killed but also the wounded, missing and captured. Total Allied casualties -- not just those killed -- have been estimated at 10,000.</p>
        <p>The article also omitted the name of the sculptor. He is James Brothers.</p>
      </block>
